14:
I see you're finally awake. It's been a
while, Rudy.
18:
Greetings, Register. I suspected you
were the one to retrieve me, but I
doubted my circuits.
19: Where might I find the Administrator?
26: The Register you know is gone too.
37:
Ah... It seems your time as a bug did
a number on your memory drive.
Least we've got you up and running.
49: "Live the way you want to live."
50: I must decide my own fate.
62:
Greetings, Stella. It is indeed a good
morning.
65:
How are you finding life in the
village, now that you have had time
to adjust?
67:
Every day I discover something new
and fascinating. I'm grateful you
welcomed me into your home.
70: Good to hear that you like it.
73: By the way, what is that?
75:
Hm? Oh! Is this perhaps your first
time seeing tea?
77: No, but... What are you doing with it?
79:
Conducting a study on taste and
how people perceive it.
82:
It is very curious. I assume the spike
in these readings is an indication of
its astringency. People find tea
pleasant to drink in spite of this... or
because of this?
84:
You could drink it and find out for
yourself.
101:
Greetings, Nimbus. You seem
energetic despite the early hour.
104:
Cut the crap! You stuck weird
electrode things all over me while I
was sleeping again!
110: I told you to stop! What the hell?!
112: I shall stop for today then.
115:
No, you'll stop FOREVER! What's the
point of torturin' me day after day?!
118:
It isn't torture. I am conducting an
observational experiment on
dreams.
121:
You tellin' me there's a point to your
shenanigans?
123:
Yes. As I cannot experience dreams
myself, I was hoping to understand
your dreams by analyzing them
through numerical data.
126:
Why me though? You coulda picked
anybody else.
128:
You have a habit of talking in your
sleep. I wished to see if your words
have any correlation with your
dreams.
132:
Stella, is she telling the truth? Do I
actually sleep talk?
136:
It's more like sleep shouting—but
yes, you do.
140:
Well, now. That's a curious
expression, Nimbus.
143: Shut it. I need some alone time.
151:
*giggle* This place is truly filled with
so many interesting subjects.
